ack\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2533115\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vpe1665702704630.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vpe1665702704630.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vpe1665702704630.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vpe1665702704630\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Transaction Control on Microsoft SQL Server\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vpe1665702704630__section_w3436ab1b5b1_w3437ab1b5_w3438ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vpe1665702704630__section_ft2_qrl_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d544263e59\">Commit and Rollback</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vpe1665702704630__p_d53066e1_d53067e1_d53068e1\">Both the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> and\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> instructions are fully supported by Microsoft SQL\n            Server.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vpe1665702704630__p_d53069e1_d53070e1_d53071e1\">Two-phase commit is not supported.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vpe1665702704630__section_asr_trl_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d544263e77\">Starting Point of a Transaction </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vpe1665702704630__p_d53075e1_d53076e1_d53077e1\">Transactions are started by the ODBC connector manager\n            when required.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vpe1665702704630__section_wqr_5rl_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d544263e86\">Implicit Rollbacks</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vpe1665702704630__p_d53081e1_d53082e1_d53083e1\">If an update or a delete causes a trigger to rollback\n            the transaction, no work is allowed on the logon path until the kernel issues a request\n            to end the transaction. This prevents users from performing work that they believe is\n            inside the transaction that has been rolled back.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"vpe1665702704630__note_d55_vrl_jcc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Users should not modify the MS-SQL triggers created\n            by Uniface.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lnt1665702561005.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Transaction Control</a><p>A transaction is a complete, logical unit of work. It usually involves adding, deleting or updating one or more logically related records in one or more databases. With Uniface, you can explicitly define a transaction with the commit ProcScript instruction. If an error occurs, a transaction can be rolled back with the rollback ProcScript instruction.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533115\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533115\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Transaction Control on Microsoft SQL Server Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Transaction Control on Microsoft SQL Server Commit and Rollback Both the commit and rollback instructions are fully supported by Microsoft SQL Server. Two-phase commit is not supported. Starting Point of a Transaction Transactions are started by the ODBC connector manager when required. Implicit Rollbacks If an update or a delete causes a trigger to rollback the transaction, no work is allowed on the logon path until the kernel issues a request to end the transaction. This prevents users from performing work that they believe is inside the transaction that has been rolled back. Note: Users should not modify the MS-SQL triggers created by Uniface. Related Links Transaction Control A transaction is a complete, logical unit of work. It usually involves adding, deleting or updating one or more logically related records in one or more databases. With Uniface, you can explicitly define a transaction with the commit ProcScript instruction. If an error occurs, a transaction can be rolled back with the rollback ProcScript instruction. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}